This is the Skynet core component, providing tools and services to remotely control one or more PlayStation DevKits.
It is meant to be imported into Python test suites or other tools.

For more info and how-to guides, see the Skynet project's home on Confluence:
https://qmjira.snei.sony.com/confluence/display/SKYN/Skynet+Home

API documentation
=================

https://github.snei.sony.com/pages/SNEI/skynet

Installation
============

Download the latest release from the "releases" tab above (or via https://github.snei.sony.com/SNEI/skynet/releases).
Get the .zip archive for Windows, and the .tar.gz for Mac/Linux.

To install the package, run in a terminal:

```
pip3 install ~/Downloads/skynet-X.Y.tar.gz
```

(substitute with skynet-X.Y.zip on Windows)

Using the Mantis test runner
============================

```
mantis-run --ip=<devkit_ip>[,<additional_devkit_ip>] path/to/tests
mantis-run --ip=<devkit_ip>[,<additional_devkit_ip>] path/to/test_file.py
mantis-run --ip=<devkit_ip>[,<additional_devkit_ip>] -k test_method
```

Tests suites
============

Tests using the Skynet core:
* https://github.snei.sony.com/SNEI/skynet-swordfish-tests
* ...

Creating the pip packages and generating the HTML API documentation
===================================================================

```
python setup.py
```

The .zip and .tar.gz packages are generated under dist/
(nb: on windows only .zip packages are generated)

The HTML API Documentation is generated under doc/_build/html.
Other document formats can be generated, see doc/Makefile for the supported formats and how to generate them.

Uploading the documentation on github
=====================================

Generate the documentation using the steps above, then switch to the gh-pages branch:

```
git checkout gh-pages
```

Put the contents of doc/_build/html into the top-level folder, then commit the changes to the branch and push to origin.
This automatically updates the documentation at https://github.snei.sony.com/pages/SNEI/skynet
